                        <summary/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="2r" to="8v"/>
                            <title ref="LIT1725Kitaba"/>
                            <note>The poem is noted in 
                                <bibl><ptr target="bm:Conti1919Harari"/><citedRange unit="page">405–406</citedRange></bibl>.
                                The title page contains the title and the name of the author (<persName ref="PRS9633UmarA" role="author"/>).
                                The language of the text is indicated with <foreign xml:lang="ha-Arab">kalām al-Ḥabaš, kalām al-Harar</foreign>. 
                                The name of the copier (<persName role="scribe" ref="PRS8156Robecchi"/>) is mentioned as
                                <foreign xml:lang="ha-Arab">Rūbīki Barakata Luwīǧī</foreign>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ha-Arab" type="inscriptio">َهَذَا كِتابُ الفَقَرْ بِكَلَامِ |الحَبَشَ بِكَلَامِ الهَرَرْ |كَتَبَ كَبِيرُ عُمَرْ عَبْدُوْشْ |غفر اللهُ ذُنُوْبَهُ | امين ا م ى ن | ا م ي ن | ا م ي ن | الحمل لله رب | العالمين | من الجهرة | هذا كتاب | مدد رُوْبيْك | بَرَكَةَ لُوِيجي</incipit>
                            <textLang mainLang="ha-Arab"/>
                        </msItem>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="11r" to="32v"/>
                            <title>ʾAlbāb an-nisāʾ</title>
                            <note>A religious chant with the title <foreign xml:lang="ha-Arab">ʾalbāb ʾan-nisāʾ</foreign> (= ‘The Hearts of the Women’),
                                similar to the one above. It likewise contains invocations of the saint Šayḫ Hāšim, as well.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="ha-Arab"/>
                        </msItem>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <locus from="33r" to="40r"/>
                            <title ref="LIT1726Kitaba"/>
                            <note>The title page contains the name of the author (<persName ref="PRS1179Abdarra" role="author"/>).
                                The language of the text is indicated with <foreign xml:lang="ha-Arab">kalām al-Ḥabaš</foreign>.
                                The poem is noted in  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Conti1919Harari"/><citedRange unit="page">406</citedRange></bibl>.
                                It shows minimal variations to the text, which was edited in 
                                <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cerulli1936Harar"/><citedRange unit="page">282–289</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="ha-Arab"/>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ha-Arab"> هذا كتاب الفرائض | بكلام الحبش اخرجه | او عبد الرحمان العراشيّ | نفعنا بهم وبنا امين | الحمد لله رن العالمين | ا م ي ن ا م ي ن | ا م ى ن | اللهم اغفر | لقارْئه | وكاتبه | وناظمه | ولسامعه | امين ا م ي ن | ا م ي ن</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        
